{
  "texts": [
    "This article aims to demonstrate how diffusion models can be used to address challenges like data scarcity and to create realistic synthetic datasets based on image synthesis.",
    "Utilizing diffusion models is a critical trend in medical imaging as synthesis data is increasingly used for training machine learning models, resulting in improved diagnostic accuracy and treatment planning.",
    "This article examines diffusion models in the context of current advancements and future possibilities in medical imaging.",
    "There are studies in medical imaging research that demonstrate accuracy of above 95%.",
    "Though, we are concerned with more than simply the accuracy of a classifier."
  ]
}